Check for Existing Implementations #Check for Existing Implementations

PHP provides a number of functions to verify existance of variables, functions, Classes and constants. All of these will return true if the entity exists.

    isset() – variables – including arrays, objects, etc.
    function_exists() – functions
    class_exists() – Classes
    defined() – constants




for installing plugins

 sudo chown -R www-data:www-data *



Folder Structure #Folder Structure

A clear folder structure helps you and others working on your plugin keep similar files together.

/plugin-name
     plugin-name.php
     uninstall.php
     /languages
     /includes
     /admin
     /admin/js
     /admin/css
     /admin/images
     /public
     /public/js
     /public/css
     /public/images
